# Semgrep exclusion list — kept to an absolute minimum.
#
# POLICY: Every exclusion must be justified and documented in SECURITY.md § Semgrep.
# Test files, utilities, and all application code are scanned. Inline nosemgrep
# annotations with documented rationale are used for false positives instead of
# blanket directory exclusions.
#
# site/ — The marketing/documentation website (Nuxt Content) is a completely
# separate application from Capacitarr with its own package.json, dependencies,
# and deployment. It has no authentication, no database access, and no API. It
# renders static HTML from trusted markdown files. Scanning it alongside the
# main application produces false positives (e.g., v-html for Mermaid SVG
# rendering) that would be addressed in a separate security review of the site
# codebase if needed.
site/
